text:
things i’d tell that kid now...
.
.
hey kid, there’s gonna be some times...wait, let’s be 💯...there’s gonna be a lot of times you’re gonna wanna give up...when you feel like this...don’t.  tell yourself everyday you’re pretty dope...there’ll be plenty of people and things in this world that will tell you otherwise.  you will change a million times throughout your life...that doesn’t mean you’re unstable...it makes you somebody that’s constantly growing and evolving ✨. you’re gonna worry about what others think about you...that’s normal...just know that what you think about yourself matters more👌🏾. you’re gonna act a fool when you’re younger 🤷🏽‍♂️, but you’re gonna turn out to be a pretty good dude...and a surprisingly good dad.  you’re gonna fall in love, break hearts, get your heart broke💔and sometimes not in that order.  it’s ok to cry, to have feelings, to share them, process them, and let them be what they are.  gender socialization is real so be the man you were born to be...not the one society tells you to be.  respect all women everywhere, recognize your blind spots, and learn to empower them 🙌🏾👸🏽💜.
.
.
and bruh...give up baseball...it’s not gonna happen...pick up a guitar and a pen and pad instead 😉🎸✍🏾🎶💜 #imabeautifulmess
.
.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
espero que exista justicia para thelma fardín (y también para calu rivero, natalia juncos y anita coacci). además, que esto sirva para profundizar el contenido que consumimos. lo que es naturalizado frente a las cámaras de televisión y lo que se oculta detrás de éstas. no hay que olvidar que el propio darthés apareció en un spot contra la violencia de género. pero algunos tienen la osadía de cuestionar el video de thelma (hablando de lágrimas de cocodrilo) en lugar de la actuación de un violador y pedófilo.

también es sabido que la gente con poder y dinero se cubren entre ellos. cuestionemos el hecho de que adrián suar haya elegido a este hombre como protagonista de una novela después de las tres primeras denuncias. que mirtha legrand lo haya invitado a su programa para defenderse (donde hablaba de ser acusado por "exceso de besos"). que mariano martínez, facundo arana, guillermo francella, entre otros, hayan salido en su defensa. que marcelo tinelli hable del caso cuando tiene un programa en el que se dedicó por años a incomodar y cosificar a mujeres.

la televisión argentina está podrida. y nosotros vemos sólo una parte desde el otro lado del cristal. no me quiero imaginar el infierno que debe ser para algunas o muchas mujeres. por eso, que se animen a hablar. siempre. porque después de este testimonio, un montón de chicas se van animando a denunciar públicamente a sus abusadores y violadores. la justicia será patriarcal, pero la condena social mancha para siempre.

que caigan todos los cómplices de este sistema patriarcal y capitalista.

#miracomonosponemos
#metoo

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
nunca más el silencio.

a todos los dartheses y eguillores: cuídense porque lo estamos tirando. 
que ardan todos los machos de todos los espacios.
banca las denuncias.
aborta a tu chongo, hermano, amigo, conocido abusador.
muerte al macho no es metáfora.
mata a tu violador.
pija violadora a la licuadora.

text:
“all kids go, but i went too soon.”-jdr
it’s amazing to be able to say that i will no longer fear the holidays the way i once did. even christmas my favorite holiday used to give me anxiety because i didn’t feel safe around relatives. for years i’d put on my holiday dresses and wool stockings while also putting up a shield. maybe for the first time in a long time i can fully enjoy this holiday and remember that in letting the truth out i am a warrior.

text:
lucka tolv
.
.
.
under lucka 12 hittar vi kärleken till organisering. 
hej, jag heter fanny westling och jobbar som journalist. en annan som jobbade som journalist var elin wägner. 
förutom vårt karriärsval delar jag och elin det fina med att ha många vänner och kollegor. elin var initiativtagare det kvinnliga journalistkollektivet ”ligan”, som verkade i början av 1900-talet. jag lärde mig om dem när jag läste boken ”ett jävla solsken”, som handlar om journalisten esther blenda nordström - tillika elin wägners bästis. (tips tips, det är den enda bok jag sträckläst sedan harry p)

ligan kämpade för att få upp sina löner, bekämpa sexism på arbetsplatsen och rätten till att rapportera om annat än ”kvinnofrågor”. samtidigt som jag läste boken rasade #metoo-hösten runt mig, och min egen bransch samlades under uppropet #deadline. 
då kände jag: fan va vi länge vi hållt på, hörni. och vi får väll fortsätta, tills de blir bra. fram tills dess ska vi göra två saker. 
a ) utbilda oss, vilket du kan göra genom att köpa kvinnoagendan. då får du ta del av 12 fantastiska kvinnoöden, däribland elin wägners som jag och illustratören @allisillus berättar om, samtidigt som du planerar ditt liv. 
b ) hjälpa de som hjälper kvinnor i nöd, och när du köper kvinnoagendan går allt överskott av försäljningen till organisationen @kvinnatillkvinna 
så, både jag och elin wägner tycker därför att alla ska köpa kvinnoagendan i julklapp, födelsedagspresent, treat-yourself-gift eller bara som en vanlig jävla kalender för 2019. den är ju trots allt resultatet av 28 kvinnor som organiserat sig.

god jul från @fanzors

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words, every day.

the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and keep abusing the faith of their fellow men. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
書籍推薦：《被隱匿的校園性犯罪》
-
最近的公投、新聞案件，讓台灣社會有一波性平教育及性犯罪的討論。這本《被隱匿的校園性犯罪》是一位日本記者對於日本校園內教師對學生的性騷擾追查報導，在聽過許多案例後，歸納讓孩子不敢開口求救的原因有老師與孩子的權力不對等，孩子往往不敢對老師說不，因為教育教導順從，或者因為從來沒有想過老師可能是會做出令人不舒服的角色而不敢向朋友、家長及其他老師求救，又可能是因為老師手上握有成績的生殺大權，而導致遺憾的事重覆發生。
.
第二個原因是因為「二次傷害」，往往被害人說出口後必須要承受「為什麼不拒絕？」、「怎麼可能？老師有老婆小孩了。」、「老師怎麼可能做這種事，是你引誘老師吧？」等言語上的二次傷害，所以讓被害人不敢開口求救。即使事情發生已過了十年、二十年，仍不敢開口，極端的例子像是直到自己的女兒又上了同一間學校，發現當年加害的老師仍任教於同間學校，才不得不開口。
.
網路的發展讓每個人的發言變得極為容易，躲在螢幕後的人們可以輕易的說出「事後想想不對勁」，但這些言語其實對被害人也是一傷害，無助於被害人受傷的心重新建立自信自尊，重新生活。輕易的發言卻擁有足以毁人一生的力量，想想令人發毛。
.
希望更多人能了解 only yes means yes，也希望孩子們能有機會從小開始了解性別教育。若發現身邊的朋友不對勁，主動關心吧！讓這樣的事情不要反覆重來，不再有下一個房思琪。
.
.

rising on a #wintersolstice ❄️ cali lili’s #debutalbum +

from cali lili indies™ 
pictures words music in motion™ 
femt0™ studi0 : 
immediate release:
venice beach, ca. – “this female is not yet rated ™ 🧜🏽‍♀️🧜‍♀️🧜🏾‍♀️ 🏄‍♀️ #calilili ’s “mostly #offthegrid ,” female fronted / produced, debut album / soundtrack, ‘this female is not yet rated ™’ drops on all music platforms this friday december 14, 2018 . 
described alternately as – a “global meditation on ‘metoo,’ “breaking the sound barriers,” an introduction to the ‘days of eve’ and ‘ not yo poppa’s holiday album, ‘ album is also the original soundtrack to cali’s indie film “eve n’god this female is not yet rated ™” ( 2019 release tba ) directed by first timer, actress / singer-songwriter cali lili from her tiny-loft studio’s handmade / home-grown label. 
the film is described as “1 day in the epiphany of a 21st century girl, who kissed a girl™” an all female-crewed, womens’ rights, #lgbtq rights, #civilrights, climate-science themed production, includes an #interracial #loveislove story based on true life incidents of violence against lgbtq / women, co-stars iconic indie spirits award nominee, #wingshauser as ‘doctor godard,’ cali lili as ‘eve,’ lifestyle coach #candaceburney as ‘lila’ and is certified “ #triplefrated ,” meaning that it was written, directed and produced by a woman, making it one of the first ( if not the first) narrative motion pictures made primarily by women. in fact, this production began promoting “all female crew” status, as far back as 2011, perhaps setting the current trend. 
the allegorical #avantgarde indie #fantasy “romance in the key of rock n’roll” is also described : “ a #rock n’ roll sci-fi dream as the global girl awakens to the legacy of herself.” © the social justice ‘rock n’ #soul’ lyrics / percussive – based soundtrack was recorded with a #diverse , #inclusive group of professional live musicians, minimal synth - ... text:
trade union rights is not given for all working men and women. in some parts of our world workers are not allowed to form a union or any other organisation. management is warning them that if anyone tries to organise workers and form a union they would be handed over to the police.

follow the swedish trade union @ifmetall to support and learn more❤ 
if metall är ett feministiskt fackförbund som står för alla människors lika rättigheter och värde, oavsett kön, sexuell läggning eller härkomst. sexuella trakasserier förekommer i alla branscher. if metall arbetar för att uppmärksamma, medvetandegöra och motverka kvinnligt förtryck och ojämställda villkor. heja! 💪
#metoo #labourunion #ifmetall #arbetsmiljö #fackligarättigheter #tradeunionrights

text:
imorgon firar vi minnet av lucia. ni vet hon som, eftersom hon vägrade gifta sig, dömdes till att arbeta på bordell och mördades för att hon stod upp för sig själv. lucia är väldigt aktuell i dessa dagar - tänk på nobels fredspris, svenska akademien, #metoo och förstås mäns våld mot kvinnor som inte tar paus. inte ens vid jul.
. 
för 17 år sen gick jag och @josefin.roos på gymnasiet och sjöng i lions luciatåg. på den tiden utsågs ortens lucia genom omröstning i lokaltidningen. det är en tradition vi i vårgårda tack och lov lämnat bakom oss. men det är ju fortfarande mysigt med ljus och sånger...
. 
vårgårda kommun kontaktade därför oss "veteraner" och frågade om vi och några till ville ställa upp och sjunga på äldreboenden, skolor, föreningsmöten och kommunfullmäktige. vi tackade ja, med ett villkor: att vi får utforma program och budskap själva och att vi får vara flexibla, eftersom vi vill kombinera uppdraget med jobb och småbarn. faktum är att kommunen betalar oss och det är bra: kvinnors arbete måste värderas högre!
. 
med vårt luciatåg solidariserar vi med kvinnor som blir offer för mäns våld, både i krig, på arbetsplatsen och i hemmet. vi slår ett slag för en jul med mindre konsumtion och alkohol, men desto mer gemenskap. vi turas om att bära kronan och stötta varandra när det blir tungt eller rösten inte håller. vi är jurister, lärare, journalister, kamrerer, industriarbetare och arbetsterapeuter som alla står upp för samma sak.
.
för det har vi blivit avbokade och utskällda på telefon. men också hyllade och uppskattade. extra roligt var det att sjunga för hem och samhälle i måndags, en förening med omkring 50 damer. tack för allt ni gör för hemmet och samhället i vårgårda ❤️

vårgårda kommun kontaktade därför oss "veteraner" och frågade om vi och några till ville ställa upp och sjunga på äldreboenden, skolor, föreningsmöten och kommunfullmäktige. vi tackade ja, med ett villkor: att vi får utforma program och budskap själva och att vi får vara flexibla, eftersom vi vill kombinera uppdraget med jobb och småbarn. faktum är att kommunen betalar oss och det är bra: kvinnors arbete måste värderas högre!
. 
med vå luciatåg solidariserar vi med kvinnor som blir offer för mäns våld, både i krig, på arbetsplatsen och i hemmet. vi slår ett slag för en jul med mindre konsumtion och alkohol, men desto mer gemenskap. vi turas om att bära kro och stötta varandra när det blir tungt eller rösten inte håller. vi är jurister, lärare, journalister, kamrerer, industriarbetare och arbetsterapeuter som alla står upp för samma sak.
.
för det har vi blivit avbokade och utskällda på telefon. men också hyllade och uppskattade. extra roligt var det att sjunga för hem och samhälle i måndags, en förening med omkring 50 damer. tack för allt ni gör för hemmet och samhället i vårgårda ❤️

text:
2018年最後にして最大の、推し本が入荷しました。

これを読まずして、未来を、社会を語ることはできません。
・
・
『私たちにはことばが必要だ フェミニストは黙らない』（タバブックス） －あなたには、自分を守る義務がある。自分を守ることは、口をひらき、声を上げることからはじまる－

2016年、韓国ソウルの江南駅で起こった女性刺殺事件。これをきっかけに、女性たちが立ち上がった。 「いまから学んでも遅くはない。一日でも早く、あなたと、新しいことばで、話がしたい」
イ・ラン(ミュージシャン、映像作家)
・
・
「おおげさだな」「極端すぎる」「どうでもいいだろう」

そんな風に、女性たちは口を塞がれてきた。

なぜ差別される側が、理解を得るために努力しなくてはならないのか？

歩み寄るつもりのない相手なら、最初から対話する義務はないし、断ってもいい。疲弊するだけか、「理解させられた」という、ほんの少しの満足感を得るだけだ。

でも言葉は、自分を、社会を守るはずだ。

どんな風に話したら、言い返したら、この思いは届くだろう。

本書は、差別や不当な扱いが蔓延する社会を生き抜くためのマニュアル書であり、心を強くするための御守りの書でもある。

どんなことにも屈しない。

we won't shut up.
・
・
装画と扉絵を手がけたのは、当店とも縁の深い、安達茉莉子。
彼女の真摯な姿勢と愚直な努力が、ここに連れてきた。
彼女ほど、この本にふさわしい人はいない。
・
・
---

text:
tenía 16 años, trabajaba en un programa de tv exitoso. la rodeaban caras agradables. conocidas. confiables. quién iba a pensar que le iba a ocurrir algo así. qué pasa con algunos hombres que no entienden que “no es no”, que no respetan el cuerpo ajeno? se alzan las voces y por momentos creo que las cosas pueden cambiar. que nuestras hijas van a vivir en una sociedad mejor. hoy hubo una nueva concientización sobre aquello que viven las mujeres cotidianamente. otras voces que se alzan. un paso más. un avance.  todavía falta mucho camino por recorrer pero qué bueno es sentir que se puede avanzar.
gracias a todas las mujeres que le ponen la voz y el cuerpo a esta lucha!!!
#noesno #mujeres #miracomonosponemos #sororidad #metoo #colectivodemujeres #nonoscallamosmas

text:
it's been a long while, really long in fact. 12 years, i think but i'm not sure and it doesn't matter. 
we were in his room and he was chirpy, bubbly and all smiles because he had a date that evening. he was in class 11, i think and it was the first time that he was going out for a date. 
we were talking about her, i mean he was telling me about her and i was patiently listening. about her, her fam, how it started and about how exactly she looked. he described her like he was here for a police sketch session. i was confused, mildly bored and wanting him to stop. 
he went ahead and told me how he was planning to do unspeakable things to her that evening and the next moment 
the 
the next moment he had his mouth on mine and a terrified 8 odd year old was feeling something. i didn't know that it wasn't cool, i didn't think. i don't know much but all i know was this is not what i wanted. he stopped when he was done. later told me he was practicing his kiss before he could actually do one. he went ahead and i was there. made to feel like this was my purpose. made to feel like i'm obliged to give in. 
i have a bleak memory otherwise, it's strange how i remember so many details about him, that day, his room and that fuckall thing that he did.
i met that asshole of a person again today. i could not bang his face on to the wall so i thought i'll tell you. 
he doesn't make eye contact with me. wonder if he remembers. really wish he does. 
#metoo

text: 365 days ago i decided to do something that would change my life forever...i spoke up. this isn’t something most people know about me, but i’m apart of the metoo movement. it was one of the hardest things i’ve ever had to do, go to my hr department and tell my story. amazingly this employee was terminated in 48 hours. my employer stood behind me every step of the way, but what i didn’t realize was the retaliation i would receive from people that i worked with for years and were considered my friends. i’ve had to rebuild myself over the past 365 days, it’s been a difficult journey, but having the loving support of my family and close friends, reassuring me that what happened to me wasn’t ok and needed to be reported. my message to the world is, know you're not alone and if something isn’t ethically or morally right stand up and say something. i did what so many people couldn’t do, and believe i’ve saved some lives in the process. so blessed to have a new work family that brings out the sunshine and laughter in me! life happens...it’s what you do with it that matters! ❤️ #metoo #oneyearlater #rebuilding

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”. cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
me produce mucho orgullo que las mujeres argentinas, sin distinción alguna, se organicen para finalmente sacarle las vendas de los ojos a nuestra sociedad y al mundo. lamentablemente, muchas tuvieron que pasar por situaciones similares a las que cuenta @soythelmafardin en el video que presentó ayer junto a actrices argentinas (deslicen ➡️), situación que fue apodada como el #metoo argentino.
así como las que pudieron denunciar antes la ayudaron a ella a contar su historia, sus palabras van a ser fuente de inspiración para muchas otras mujeres que aun sufren acosos, abusos, situaciones de violencia y violaciones en silencio. deconstruyamos la sociedad machista que permitió todo esto en cada espacio que podamos. es apoderándonos de las calles y de nuestras propias voces que terminaremos con la impunidad ✊🏻💚 se va a caer.
mirá el hashtag #miracomonosponemos para ver más publicaciones al respecto!

text:
👉el #muvondehoy me dice que la palabra lucha no refleja la verdadera consciencia que se está despertando entre las mujeres😔la lucha no es justa, no muestra todo nuestro empoderamiento que no proviene solamente del enojo. proviene del saberse acompañada🧡hoy podemos decir la verdad y por ende la sororidad es lo que debería definirnos como #tribu.
🌟esta foto es de ayer, pero la subo hoy porque puedo. y porque merezco levantarme a la mañana y decir todas podemos: estar vivas, hacer lo que tengamos ganas, ser fuertes o sensibles. todas tenemos el derecho de ser como nos salga ser.
✔por todas las veces que me dijeron que me calle.
✔por todas las veces que me dijeron "si sos más simpática que linda, ¿quién te va a creer que tu jefe te sigue con la camioneta hasta santa fé y godoy cruz?"
✔por todas las veces que me dijeron "seguro te gusta"
✔por todas las veces que corrí
✔por las clases de boxeo
✔por la ira contenida que me enfermó
✔por tener una cuchilla a mano
✔por el tabique roto y la cara con cicatrices
✔por la policía que dijo que si a los 15 hacía esa denuncia qué me quedaba para los 20
✔porque no soy "loca" porque coordino a 10 hombres
✔porque sea cual sea mi trabajo no merezco que te encierres en mi oficina a acosarme o que me encierres en la tuya o me hagas una emboscada camino al baño
✔por mi miedo a la oscuridad
✔porque mi pelo es mi pelo. mi piel es mi piel y mis decisiones son mías (ni te cuento mi cuerpo) ✔por los años de terapia porque yo tenía 7 años y me hicieron esconder
✔por todas. por todo
✔porque hay gente que no va a cambiar nunca pero nosotras ya cambiamos
✔porque no estoy lista para escribir nombres acá abajo pero sí tengo todas las herramientas para abrazar a mis hermanas
✔porque nos pasó a casi todas: #sororidad

text:
helpless and abused.
_
would you treat a #dog this way?
_
dairy’s dark secret
the typical dairy cow on a farm produces nearly 22,000 pounds of milk a year – more than double­ what its forebears did 40 years ago. they never graze; their hooves have rotted from standing in their own filth. 
_
cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; “so common,” “seen guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‘i totally got her in the eyeball!’ it’s what happens when you do this long enough. they’re not your fellow creatures, they’re just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can’t get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. “he got sick and gave up,” and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock". it’s like they hate their own animals for having feelings.”
_
how can you possibly justify this for a glass of milk, a piece of cheese, a bowl of #icecream?there are so many plant-based alternatives available. please choose wisely. will your choices be responsible for creating more victims?

cows, like pigs, are social creatures; their babies are even more so. they nuzzle strangers, groan with pleasure when you pet them, and attach without complaint to callous minders. their sweetness gets them nowhere at auctions or at farms, however; the men and women working here smack them with boards and kick them in the haunches to move them forward. as one undercover investigator stated; “so common,” “seen guys punch them, stick cattle prods in their eyes, bragging, ‘i totally got her in the eyeball!’ it’s what happens when you do this long enough. they’re not your fellow creatures, they’re just trouble.
_
then there's the baby...a calf that can’t get up. its velveteen eyes are wet but blank; he barely stirs when jostled by other calves. “he got sick and gave up,” and so it goes with farmers who gave up farming to become cruel jailers of their "stock". it’s like they hate their own animals for having feelings.”
_

la actriz radicó la denuncia penal en la fiscalía de género de nicaragua, ya que la presentación judicial debe hacerse en el lugar donde ocurrió el abuso. ▪️thelma relató los hechos en un conmovedor video: “durante nueve años mantuve en silencio lo que me pasó hasta que otra chica lo denuncio", empezó.
▪️juan darthés podría ser extraditado si la justicia nicaragüense lo solicita al gobierno argentino.más de 20 años de prisión podrían esperar al actor  si nicaragua lo declarara culpable de la violación después que el poder legislativo de esta nación centroamericana.
.

.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words, every day.

the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
only a week after the nationwide strike, a 25th woman was found murdered. imad ahmed awad, of 29 years old, the same age i am, was found with stabbing wounds in her apartment. 
as long as the state is absent in the act of protecting us and preventing violence, as long as our society still considers our lives don’t matter, the government will keep on being responsible for every death woman, for every femicide, for every rape, for every life lost. we are done with learning how to live in/with fear or how to defend ourselves for every possible attack. our society should just learn how to respect women’s lives. 
these are some pictures of this morning strike in tel aviv. 
worldwide patriarchy is falling because we are tearing it down, and it will fall, sister, yes it will.

text:
there's a man back a-ways
who believes at where he is
and there's a girl
up ahead who says she knows

and the street overflows
with the folk who understand
but for the guy who can't be seen
he's the shadow man

and the shadow man is close at hand

take a turn and see his smile
made of nothing but loneliness
just take a walk and be a friend
to the shadow man

you can call him joe, you can call him sam
you should call and see who answers
for he promises to come running, guided by the truth

but the shadow man is really you

look in his eyes and see your reflection
look to the stars and see his eyes
he'll show you tomorrow, he'll show you the sorrows
of what you did today

you can call him foe, you can call him friend
you should call and see who answers
for he knows your eyes are drawn to the road ahead

and the shadow man is waiting round the bend
shadow man
waiting up the bend
shadow man
waiting up the bend
waiting up the bend

david bowie

text:
yo te creo! 
yo te creo, claro que te creo. a vos y a todas las que desde las vísceras, desde el alma, desde las entrañas, desde los años sufridos, desde la vergüenza, desde el honor mutilado tienen algo por decir y por denunciar. 
yo te creo, porque desde la amenaza, el miedo, la vergüenza, el asco, el sentir que "algo habrán hecho" ,puede algún canalla suelto, (que son muchos pero son los menos),:
desde la manipulación pueden con una que sufre, que se asusta, que es gigante pero se siente chiquita.
pero sin duda, no pueden los canallas,no pueden con tod@s, no pueden con las voces que se levantan, no pueden con oídos que escuchan, no pueden con una historia que tendría que haber cambiado hace mucho pero está cambiando ahora, 
y digo , digo desde el cuero y desde el cuore, ¡yo te creo!
nunca más te calles, nunca más pienses que te lo mereces, nunca más , no es no, tu cuerpo es tuyo y nadie puede rozarte siquiera si vos decís que no. 
contá conmigo,y con muchos más, no estas sola.
"tu no puedes volver atrás, porque la vida ya te empuja como un aullido interminable, interminable..."
yo te creo...
#yotecreo #miracomonosponemos #niunamenos #metoo #basta

text:
recuerdo cuando tenía 13 años volviendo a casa caminando después de jugar volleyball una bestia inadaptada, frena, saca la mano de su taxi y me estruja la cola al pasar. .
estaba sola, me quede helada, ese momento, sentí vergüenza, rabia, incomodidad, sentía que habían golpeado mi dignidad, me puse a llorar al caminar (era una niña!). la sensación es horrible y no puedo imaginar lo que uno sentirá en situaciones peores.
.
y ni contar todas las veces de acoso callejero... no somos objeto de nadie! basta! .
si sufrieron o sufren abuso, no se callen! puede ser que esa bestia siga haciendo lo mismo a otras personas y lo pueden evitar.
.
#miracomonosponemos #niunamenos #metoo

text:
un susurro libidinoso, una mano inesperada, una mirada inadecuada, un roce inapropiado, una frase desafortunada, un algo que no pedimos ni queremos. cuando nos pasa, el miedo nos cierra la boca. la vergüenza nos hace bajar la mirada y mordernos la lengua. pensar que hicimos algo para provocarlo, que algo de culpa tenemos. sentir que es inevitable que suceda en algún momento. advertirle a nuestras hijas de las situaciones que se le pueden presentar en la vida, en la calle, en el transporte público, en el boliche... porque nos pasó y es casi seguro que en algún momento también les pase. qué mierda. hoy tengo el recuerdo fresco de esos momentos en mi adolescencia. y hoy recuerdo cómo los guardé para mí por vergüenza. y los archivé en la memoria, como parte del equipaje que uno está destinado a llevar, bajo el consuelo de "a todas les pasa algo así". qué mierda.
pero la mierda sale a flote. hoy estamos aprendiendo a alzar la voz, a vencer el miedo y hablar, gritar, protestar, denunciar. a que la vergüenza no nos paralice, porque mordernos la lengua sólo nos trae dolor. no es no, y no acepta libres interpretaciones. no es no, y no requiere de más explicaciones. no es no, y no hace falta tener que repetirlo una y otra vez. no es no, y no debería hacer falta tener que decirlo. enseñemos el mismo idioma a nuestros hijos varones y mujeres. no es no para cualquiera, en cualquier lugar, bajo cualquier circunstancia. 
#miracomonosponemos #yotecreo #metoo #noesno
